#week-title("Three", "Collecting the Volatile: Fermented Distillates")

=== Core Teaching

A fermented distillate differs significantly from a simple distillate. Through
putrefaction, the "fixed" has been partially "volatilised," allowing new
fractions to rise that were previously trapped in the earthy matrix.

This week, collect the volatile fraction from your fermented plant matter or
water. Observe the sensory differences: the scent should be sharper and the liquid
should exhibit a different "vitality" than your Month 9 vegetable hydrosols.

=== Topics This Week

- Differences between simple and fermented distillates
- Collecting the "volatile from the fixed"
- Reading the signs of progress in the distillate

#inner-work[
  *The Breath of the Raven*

  Continue the Threefold Breath practice from Year One. As you breathe in, imagine
  you are drawing in the sharpened Mercury of your fermented preparation.

  Does the breath feel different this month? Is there a sense of "clearing" or
  "stripping away" that corresponds to the action of the fermented spirit? Record
  your findings in your journal.
]

